FBIS3-52884 "drnes006_r_94005" FBIS-NES-94-006 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Jan 1994 India CPI Criticizes U.S. for Pakistani Exercises BK0801160894 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 GMT 8 Jan 94 BK0801160894 Delhi All India Radio Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The CPI [Communist Party of India] has criticized the United States for conducting joint armed exercises with Pakistan. In a press statement in New Delhi today, the party national executive said that the Clinton administration is only supporting militarist elements in Islamabad by this action. The party said that the U.S. by having exercises with Pakistan is lending direct support to the terrorists in the Kashmir valley. The party also criticized an anti-India letter to a Kashmiri separatist outfit by the American president.
